      "role": "user",
      "content": "can u finish that last point about third-party claims? i'm also just worried about stuff being buried in the fine print that i might not notice unless i'm looking for it. like, is there a way to spot those \"sneaky\" parts of a contract?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly, let's finish that point.\n\n6. Third-Party Claims: Indemnification clauses can sometimes extend beyond just the parties involved in the agreement. If the Disclosing Party's actions or the information shared under the NDA lead to a lawsuit from a third party who wasn't part of the contract, they may still try to hold you responsible under the indemnification clause. This aspect of the clause can be quite \"sneaky\" because it might not be immediately obvious that third-party claims are included.\n\nAs for spotting \"sneaky\" parts of a contract, here are some tips:\n\n- **Read Thoroughly**: Always read the entire agreement, not just the sections you're most interested in. Details in the fine print can have significant implications.\n\n- **Ask Questions**: If you're unsure about any part of the contract, don't hesitate to ask for clarification from the other party or seek legal advice.\n\n- **Summarize Key Points**: As you read, summarize the key obligations, rights, and responsibilities in your own words to ensure you understand them.\n\n- **Look for Ambiguities**: Be wary of vague language or broad terms that could be interpreted in different ways.\n\n- **Check for Consistencies**: Compare different sections",
      "source": "target",
